  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0d9c\u0db8\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2\u0da7 \u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dba \u0daf\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Give the Prime Minister time",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Palani Digambaran, the Nuwara Eliya District MP of the Samagi Jana Balawegaya, said that the Prime Minister should be given time to resolve the issues of the country and that there was no point in blaming Ranil Wickremesinghe who took over as the Prime Minister when no one else accepted him.",
        "Mr. Tigambaran also said that even if Sajith Premadasa takes over the country tomorrow or Anura Kumara takes over, even if the whole parliament convenes, it will not be possible to resolve the issues immediately.",
        "He said that since it was a bankrupt country, no one could solve the problems in two or three weeks, adding that the Prime Minister should be given at least another two months.",
        "Speaking to the media after meeting the Indian High Commissioner in Sri Lanka, Palani Thigambaran said that he had met the Indian High Commissioner in Sri Lanka and told him about the suffering of the Sri Lankan people.",
        "He also met the Prime Minister and informed him of the suffering of the people in the plantation areas.",
        "Mr. India has been assisting Sri Lanka so far and will continue to do so, he said.",
        "He said the crisis would not be resolved as long as Gotabhaya was in power."
      ],
